<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1446,1761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on a molecular analysis by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sigwart, J. D. &amp; Schwabe, E. &amp; Saito, H. &amp; Samadi, S. &amp; Giribet, G." box="[705,939,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" pagination="560 - 572" refId="ref18930" refString="Sigwart, J. D., Schwabe, E., Saito, H., Samadi, S. &amp; Giribet, G. (2010) Evolution in the deep sea: a combined analysis of the earliest diverging living chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida). Invertebrate Systematics, 24, 560 - 572. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 10028" type="journal article" year="2010">Sigwart et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[1065,1199,1555,1581]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1199,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not monophyletic. Morphological studies of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[558,692,1591,1617]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[558,692,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed some groups of species that possess a set of similar features, which include the shell, girdle, radula, and gills. Most of these groups inhabit a more or less restricted area, but several groups, mainly of deep-water leptochitons, are widely distributed in the world oceans. Probably the first species of each of these groups originated from different ancestors of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1889" box="[1074,1256,1699,1725]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Leptochitonidae</taxonomicName>
resulting in the polyphyletic character of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[552,686,1735,1761]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,686,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
